    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "Imam al-Baqir (AS) describes a vivid eschatological scene on the Day of Resurrection where the days of the week will be personified and brought forth before all creation. Friday is depicted as their leader, radiant with light and likened to a noble bride, serving as a witness for those who attended the Friday prayer. The hadith emphasizes that the rank of believers entering Paradise will correspond to their devotion to Friday prayer.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الجمعة": "Friday (Jumu'ah) — the day of congregational prayer in Islam, considered the best day of the week",
          "ساطع": "Dazzling/radiant — indicating Friday's special luminous status on the Day of Judgment",
